$ Python library: Setuptools
@ setuptools

`setuptools` enhances `→ development/languages/Python/standard-library/distutils` so as to make it easier to build and distribute Python packages.

? setuptools is not part of the → development/languages/Python/standard-library, but comes with `→ development/languages/Python/installation/directory/Scripts/pip` (and is found quite ubiquitously).

sa:

 The standard library `→ development/languages/Python/standard-library/distutils`.

 → development/languages/Python#py-packaging

  → development/languages/Python/PEP/0517[PEP 517]

